commit.message: Move PPrintMini.ml to a separate directory.

Remove [make menhir], which is not needed.

Instead, switch to the branch [vendor] and use [make vendor].
Makefile changes to deal with the new benchmark.
Documentation: warn about the complexity of [ifflat].
Simplify [make test] so that it does not mysteriously need js_of_ocaml.

Require OCaml 4.03 or newer.

[@inline] annotations are otherwise rejected.
Add a few [@inline] annotations. Eta-expand some functions.

Alter the smart constructors so as to recognize empty documents.

This can make construction slightly slower, but offers a basis
for an efficient implementation of [is_empty].

Require OCaml 4.02.3.

We get a syntax error when compiling PPrint with OCaml 4.02.0.
This should fix issue #8.
Recreate the type [representation], without documenting it.
